reviewText: Since I have always worked in startups I have had to wear multiple hats. I was reinventing the wheel again and again because I was working across multiple departments. This meant thinking of a solution for removing inefficiencies even if they were human resources related myself. So I came up with perfromance reviews but the learning would have been a lot faster if such tools are given to new managers at the beginning of their journey.   I have learned to recommend courses already available to new managers. Also have a coaching culture so that the team also accepts the new manager easily instead of the manager focusing on performance only. Would have been great to receive a certificate as well.

reviewText: I thought I knew everything on management because I had done short entrepreneurial courses on the subject  and I had emotional intelligence. I did not expect this course to teach me anything new. But I have to admit that I was floored. It had many new things to teach me. Practices that I thought I was getting right, but I wasn't, for example creating a framework to hire the right fit for one's company. I am very happy I took this course.
